  "ruleSummary1Title": "Objective",
  "ruleSummary1Body": "Complete collective farm jobs while protecting your private plot. Highest score wins!",
  "ruleSummary2Title": "Gameplay",
  "ruleSummary2Body": "Play cards to tricks - must follow lead suit if able.",
  "ruleSummary3Title": "Jobs",
  "ruleSummary3Body": "Jobs need 40 work hours to complete.",
  "ruleSummary4Title": "Trump Face Cards",
  "ruleSummary4Body": "Jack, Queen, and King have special powers in nomenclature games.",
  "ruleSummary5Title": "Scoring",
  "ruleSummary5Body": "Cards in your plot equal your score. Highest score wins.",
  "ruleSummary6Title": "Work",
  "ruleSummary6Body": "Win tricks, then assign captured cards to matching jobs.",
  "ruleSummary7Title": "Protect",
  "ruleSummary7Body": "Keep plot cards safe from failed-job requisition.",
  "ruleSummary8Title": "Trump faces",
  "ruleSummary8Body": "Jack goes north, Queen exposes, King doubles exile.",
  "tutorialStep1Title": "Welcome to the collective",
  "tutorialStep1Body": "This is a real game, comrade — play while we talk. Your goal: end the Five-Year Plan with the most points hidden in your cellar.",
  "tutorialStep1Tip": "High hidden cards are your bank. Losing one to the North can swing the final score.",
  "tutorialStep1Callout": "The buttons below turn my lessons. The board stays yours.",
  "tutorialStep2Title": "Read the work board",
  "tutorialStep2Body": "Four jobs each year, one per crop. Each reward pile has ranks 1–4 plus one hidden lotto rank from 5–K; the counter is work hours — 40 completes the job.",
  "tutorialStep2Tip": "Failed jobs summon requisition at year's end. Remember which crops look doomed.",
  "tutorialStep2Callout": "Find the four job counters along the top of the table.",
  "tutorialStep3Title": "The trump crop",
  "tutorialStep3Body": "In planning, one crop is declared the State's main task — trump. In year five, the leftover deal card is revealed to set trump; Saboteur means no trump.",
  "tutorialStep3Tip": "Pick trump for the hand you expect to play, not only for the biggest card you see.",
  "tutorialStep3Callout": "Waiting for trump to be declared…",
  "tutorialStep4Title": "Play a card",
  "tutorialStep4Body": "Follow the led crop if you can — legal cards glow. Out of that crop? Play anything, even trump.",
  "tutorialStep4Tip": "Ducking a trick is allowed — and often wise. Winners attract attention.",
  "tutorialStep4Callout": "Play a card from your hand when your turn comes.",
  "tutorialStep5Title": "Taking the trick",
  "tutorialStep5Body": "Highest card of the led crop wins — unless trump lands; then the highest trump. The winner takes a medal and becomes brigade leader.",
  "tutorialStep5Tip": "Medals break ties at the end — but every win paints a target on your cellar.",
  "tutorialStep5Callout": "Watch who takes this trick.",
  "tutorialStep6Title": "Assign the labor",
  "tutorialStep6Body": "The brigade leader sends the trick's cards to jobs — only crops present in the trick are legal targets. A card's rank is its hours.",
  "tutorialStep6Tip": "Assign work to protect the crops that match your best cellar cards.",
  "tutorialStep6Callout": "When you win a trick, tap its cards onto jobs.",
  "tutorialStep7Title": "Meet the quota",
  "tutorialStep7Body": "A job that reaches 40 hours is complete: its reward drops into the closer's cellar, and that crop is safe from requisition this year.",
  "tutorialStep7Tip": "A finished job pays you and protects you. Two birds, one quota.",
  "tutorialStep7Callout": "Push a job to 40 hours to claim its reward.",
  "tutorialStep8Title": "The leftover card",
  "tutorialStep8Body": "Only four tricks are played. Your fifth card slips face-down into your cellar at year's end — its rank becomes points.",
  "tutorialStep8Tip": "Steer the year so your best card is the one that survives.",
  "tutorialStep8Callout": "Your unplayed card banks itself when the year ends.",
  "tutorialStep9Title": "This is requisition",
  "tutorialStep9Body": "If N crop suits fail, each vulnerable player loses their N highest cellar cards across those suits. Party Official adds one; Drunkard removes its suit from the quota.",
  "tutorialStep9Tip": "Never won a trick? Nothing to confess. Cowardice has its rewards.",
  "tutorialStep9Callout": "Read the requisition report carefully.",
  "tutorialStep10Title": "The yearly swap",
  "tutorialStep10Body": "From year two, you may trade one hand card for one cellar card before the trick begins.",
  "tutorialStep10Tip": "Bury high cards while they are safe; pull out crops that look doomed.",
  "tutorialStep10Callout": "Consider your swap before the trick begins.",
  "tutorialStep11Title": "Beware the Wrecker",
  "tutorialStep11Body": "One joker hides among the workers: he follows any suit and brings 0 hours — and any job holding him fails inspection.",
  "tutorialStep11Tip": "Win him boldly, bury him bitterly — or make him someone else's problem.",
  "tutorialStep11Callout": "He plays by Kolkhoz rules — watch for the wild card.",
  "tutorialStep12Title": "Year five is famine",
  "tutorialStep12Body": "The last year is lean: four cards, three tricks, no trump at all. Short, and usually decisive.",
  "tutorialStep12Tip": "Save flexible high cards for famine; without trump a bad lead is hard to escape.",
  "tutorialStep12Callout": "Waiting for the famine year…",
  "tutorialStep13Title": "Highest final cellar wins",
  "tutorialStep13Body": "After year five, every cellar card counts its rank. Highest total wins the Plan; medals break ties. Make me proud, comrade.",
  "tutorialStep13Tip": "One protected King is worth a year of caution.",
  "tutorialStep13Callout": "Finish the Plan — Misha is watching.",
